{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddafed2f3-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s9"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"9"},"text":"§ 9.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Additional examiners, clerks, and other employees","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Comptroller of the Currency is authorized to employ such additional examiners, clerks, and other employees as he deems necessary to carry out the provisions of sections 4, 6, 9, 10, 1151 to 1318, and 1322 of this title and to assign to duty in the office of his bureau in Washington such examiners and assistant examiners as he shall deem necessary to assist in the performance of the work of that bureau.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddafed2f4-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1923-03-04/ch252"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923, ch. 252","children":[],"tail":", title II, § 209(b), "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/42/1467"},"text":"42 Stat. 1467","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddafed2f5-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddafed2f6-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddafed2f7-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 6, referred to in text, was repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/251/s1/c/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–251, § 1(c)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-09-09"},"text":"Sept. 9, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/488"},"text":"73 Stat. 488","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 1151, 1161 to 1163, 1171, 1172, 1181, 1182, 1191, 1201, 1202, 1211 to 1215, 1221 to 1223, 1231, 1232, 1241 to 1244, 1246, 1247, 1249, 1251, 1261, 1271, 1281 to 1283, 1291 to 1293, 1301 to 1303, and 1322 of this title, included within the reference to sections 1151 to 1318, and 1322 of this title, were repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/86/230/s24"},"text":"Pub. L. 86–230, § 24","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1959-09-08"},"text":"Sept. 8, 1959","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/73/466"},"text":"73 Stat. 466","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section 1151a, included within the reference to sections 1151 to 1318 of this title, was repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/92/181/tV/s5"},"text":"Pub. L. 92–181, title V, § 5","children":[],"tail":".26(a), "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1971-12-10"},"text":"Dec. 10, 1971","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/85/624"},"text":"85 Stat. 624","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Sections 1245, 1248, and 1311 to 1318, included within the reference to sections 1151 to 1318 of this title, were repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1948-06-25/ch645/s21"},"text":"act June 25, 1948, ch. 645, § 21","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/62/862"},"text":"62 Stat. 862","children":[],"tail":", eff. "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1948-09-01"},"text":"Sept. 1, 1948","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The bureau referred to in text is known as the Office of the Comptroller of the Currency.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddafed2f8-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section is comprised of subsec. (b), third sentence, of section 209 of act ","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1923-03-04"},"text":"Mar. 4, 1923","children":[],"tail":". For classification to this title of other provisions of section 209, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"execDoc","id":"iddafed2f9-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Executive Documents","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"miscellaneous","id":"iddafed2fa-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Exception as to Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Functions vested by any provision of law in Comptroller of the Currency, referred to in this section, not included in transfer of functions to Secretary of the Treasury, see note set out under ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1"},"text":"section 1 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
